        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "adilger@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-06-05 15:29:36.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-1402 libcfs: CFS_ALLOC_HIGH is __GFP_HIGHMEM",
        "message": "LU-1402 libcfs: CFS_ALLOC_HIGH is __GFP_HIGHMEM\n\nAccording to the comment above CFS_ALLOC_HIGH, the flag\nallows allocator to return memory in the highmen zone, but\ncfs_alloc_flags_to_gfp() incorrectly converts it to\n__GFP_HIGH, which enables the use of emergency pools.\n\n__GFP_HIGHMEM should be used instead. Also it makes sense to rename\nCFS_ALLOC_HIGH to CFS_ALLOC_HIGHMEM to avoid further confusion.\n\nSigned-off-by: Isaac Huang <Isaac_Huang@xyratex.com>\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I088f36faec1fe22902065d680730731f8deab5d2\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
